# F15.OBJ - the OWL FLY II fighter, hand-built for the OBJ2DAT pipeline.
# Convert with:  OBJ2DAT F15.OBJ F15.DAT 2   (2 units per metre)
#
# Axes as Blender exports: -Z forward, Y up; OBJ2DAT maps engine Z = -obj Z.
# The nose therefore points to obj -Z here, and the engine sees +Z.
#
# CONTRACT WITH THE WRECK POOL: the game's explosion debris is cut from
# the OLD fighter's face table over THIS model's first 13 vertices, so
# vertices 1..13 below keep the classic meanings: nose, rear top L/R,
# rear bottom L/R, wingtip L/R, wing root fore, wing rear L/R, fin
# base/top/rear (the left fin of the twin tail plays the classic fin).
# Everything after 13 is new geometry: the forward fuselage, the canopy,
# the right fin, the aft wingtips.
#
# Materials are absolute palette indices (PALnn): 24 sun-lit white,
# 16 shade, 25 mid grey, 00 light grey wings, 04 canopy glass,
# 94 the palette-cycled engine fire.
v 0 0.5 -11
v -1.5 1 6
v 1.5 1 6
v -1.5 -0.5 6
v 1.5 -0.5 6
v -6.5 0.5 2
v 6.5 0.5 2
v 0 0.5 -3
v -1.5 0.5 5
v 1.5 0.5 5
v -1.5 1 3
v -2 4 7
v -1.5 1 6
v -1 1 -5
v 1 1 -5
v -1 -0.5 -5
v 1 -0.5 -5
v 0 2 -2
v 1.5 1 3
v 2 4 7
v 1.5 1 6
v -6.5 0.5 4.5
v 6.5 0.5 4.5
usemtl PAL24
f 1 14 15
f 14 15 3 2
usemtl PAL16
f 1 16 17
f 16 17 5 4
usemtl PAL25
f 1 14 16
f 1 15 17
f 14 2 4 16
f 15 3 5 17
usemtl PAL00
f 8 6 22 9
f 8 7 23 10
usemtl PAL04
f 14 18 15
usemtl PAL25
f 11 12 13
f 19 20 21
usemtl PAL94
f 2 3 5 4
